1 AN ACT concerning traffic regulations; relating to speed limits; permitting
2 local authorities with jurisdiction over residence districts to reduce the
3 maximum speed limit to 25 miles per hour in their respective residence
4 districts without an engineering and traffic investigation; amending
5 K.S.A. 8-1560 and repealing the existing section.
6
7 Be it enacted by the Legislature of the State of Kansas:
8 Section 1. K.S.A. 8-1560 is hereby amended to read as follows: 8-
9 1560. (a) Whenever local authorities in their respective jurisdictions
10 determine on the basis of an engineering and traffic investigation that the
11 maximum speed permitted is greater or less than is reasonable and safe
12 under the conditions found to exist upon a highway or part of a highway,
13 the local authority may determine and declare a reasonable and safe
14 maximum limit thereon which that:
15 (1) Decreases the limit at intersections;
16 (2) increases the limit within an urban district but does not to exceed
17 the maximum speed of 65 miles per hour;
18 (3) decreases the limit outside an urban district, but not to not less
19 than 20 miles per hour, except as authorized by K.S.A. 8-1560a, and
20 amendments thereto;
21 (4) decreases the limit within an urban district in a school zone to not
22 less than 20 miles per hour, except that any such decreased limit shall
23 apply only during the hours in which students are normally en route to or
24 from school,. Such zones and hours to shall be determined by ordinance or
25 resolution of such local authority; or
26 (5) decreases the limit within any residence district, but not to not less
27 than 20 miles per hour.
28 (b) Except as provided in subsection (h), local authorities in their
29 respective jurisdictions may determine by an engineering and traffic
30 investigation the proper maximum speed for all arterial streets and shall
31 declare a reasonable and safe maximum limit thereon which that may be
32 greater or less than the maximum speed permitted under this act for an
33 urban district or other location in which the arterial street is situated,
34 except that in no event shall any local authority establish any such
35 maximum limit in excess of 65 miles per hour.

