1 (c) Except as otherwise provided in paragraph (4) of subsection (a)
2 (4), any altered limit established as authorized shall be effective at all
3 times or during hours of darkness or at other times as may be determined
4 when appropriate signs giving notice thereof are erected upon such street
5 or highway.
6 (d) Any alteration of maximum limits on city connecting links shall
7 not be effective until such alteration has been approved by the secretary of
8 transportation.
9 (e) If local authorities in their respective jurisdictions have
10 established a speed limit within any residence district which that is less
11 than 30 miles per hour, prior to the effective date of this act, such speed
12 limit shall be deemed valid and shall not require an engineering and traffic
13 investigation.
14 (f) Local authorities in their respective jurisdictions may establish the
15 speed limit within a road construction zone, as defined in K.S.A. 8-1458a,
16 and amendments thereto, upon any highway under the jurisdiction of such
17 local authorities.
18 (g) The provisions of K.S.A. 8-1560b, and amendments thereto, shall
19 apply to the limitations on speed limits provided by subsection (a) of this
20 section.
21 (h) Local authorities who have jurisdiction over county or township
22 highways may determine, based on an engineering and traffic investigation
23 or without an engineering and traffic investigation, the proper maximum
24 speed for such county or township highways and shall declare a reasonable
25 and safe maximum limit thereon which that may be greater or less than the
26 maximum speed permitted under this act, except that in no event shall any
27 local authority establish any such maximum limit in excess of 65 miles per
28 hour.
29 (i) Local authorities who have jurisdiction over city residence
30 districts may reduce the maximum speed limit in their respective residence
31 districts to 25 miles per hour without the engineering and traffic
32 investigation required by subsection (a).
33 Sec. 2. K.S.A. 8-1560 is hereby repealed.
34 Sec. 3. This act shall take effect and be in force from and after its
35 publication in the statute book.

